{"body": "Here is a sample use-case :\r\n\r\nI want to build a simple search action, but I would like to be able to call scopes on my model based on what's in the query string.\r\n\r\nFor example : /messages?scopes=archived,moderated\r\n\r\nI need to be sure the values in ``params[:messages]`` are scopes before calling them.\r\n\r\n", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/21251155", "created_at": "2013-07-19T14:03:18Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/11503#issuecomment-21251155", "updated_at": "2013-07-19T14:03:18Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 11503, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Intrepidd/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Intrepidd/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Intrepidd/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/Intrepidd", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Intrepidd/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/Intrepidd", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Intrepidd/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/ce1485ded3e4bc49709eb25e0522a657?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F3344bb1b8d20cc68a3f691ef9458bae5.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Intrepidd/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Intrepidd/received_events", "gravatar_id": "ce1485ded3e4bc49709eb25e0522a657", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Intrepidd/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "Intrepidd", "type": "User", "id": 803765, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Intrepidd/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5237d3babd3543c151007fd9"}, "id": 21251155, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/11503"}
